<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-07-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-07-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="16" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d16">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">King of Belgium</gloss> to
                                President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-07-02"><hi rend="italic">July 2,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I am very much grieved at the death of Mr. Hay, and wish to express to
                            you, Mr. President, my sincere condolences, and to assure you of my keen
                            sympathy with you in your bereavement and that of the American
                            people.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Leopold.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>